<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    {% if env == 'dev' %}  
    <title>Terraform & Ansible Learning from DEV environment</title>
    {% else %}
    <title>Terraform & Ansible Learning</title>
    {% endif %}
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        .header {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 40px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .code-block {
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        .comparison-table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .comparison-table th, .comparison-table td {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: left;
        }
        .comparison-table th {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Understanding Terraform and Ansible</h1>
            {% if env == 'dev' %}
            <p style="color: red;">You are currently viewing the DEV environment</p>
            {% endif %}
            <p>Infrastructure as Code (IaC) and Configuration Management Tools</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Terraform Overview</h2>
            <p>Terraform is an Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tool that allows you to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Define infrastructure using declarative configuration files</li>
                <li>Create and manage resources across multiple cloud providers</li>
                <li>Track infrastructure state</li>
                <li>Automate infrastructure provisioning</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>
# Example Terraform Configuration
provider "aws" {
    region = "us-west-2"
}

resource "aws_instance" "example" {
    ami           = "ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"
    
    tags = {
        Name = "Example Instance"
    }
}</pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Ansible Overview</h2>
            <p>Ansible is a configuration management and automation tool that:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Uses YAML syntax for playbooks</li>
                <li>Requires no agents on managed nodes</li>
                <li>Operates over SSH</li>
                <li>Provides idempotent execution</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>
# Example Ansible Playbook
---
- name: Configure web server
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes
  
  tasks:
    - name: Install nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present
        
    - name: Start nginx service
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started</pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Comparison: Terraform vs Ansible</h2>
            <table class="comparison-table">
                <tr>
                    <th>Feature</th>
                    <th>Terraform</th>
                    <th>Ansible</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Primary Use</td>
                    <td>Infrastructure Provisioning</td>
                    <td>Configuration Management</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Language</td>
                    <td>HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language)</td>
                    <td>YAML</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>State Management</td>
                    <td>Maintains state files</td>
                    <td>Stateless</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Architecture</td>
                    <td>Pull-based</td>
                    <td>Push-based</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Best Practices</h2>
            <h3>Terraform Best Practices</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Use remote state storage</li>
                <li>Implement state locking</li>
                <li>Use workspaces for environment separation</li>
                <li>Version control your configurations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Ansible Best Practices</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Use roles for organization</li>
                <li>Keep playbooks simple and focused</li>
                <li>Use variables and templates</li>
                <li>Implement proper inventory management</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Integration Example</h2>
            <p>Using Terraform and Ansible together:</p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>
# Terraform provisioning with Ansible integration
resource "aws_instance" "web" {
    ami           = "ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"

    provisioner "local-exec" {
        command = "ansible-playbook -i '${self.public_ip},' configure-web.yml"
    }
}</pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>